Greek Credit-Default Swaps Jump 52 Basis Points to Record 1,102

-- B y   M i c h a e l   S h a n a h a n
-- 
2011-04-14T13:50:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/greek-credit-default-swaps-jump-52-basis-points-to-record-1-102.html
The cost of insuring Greek
government debt jumped 52 basis points to a record 1,102,
according to CMA prices for credit-default swaps. Contracts on
 Portugal  rose 15 basis points to 593.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Shanahan at 
 mshanahan3@bloomberg.net  